# 1. Create a dictionary to store information about 5 cities in Karnataka and their famous dishes.Add a new city and its dish to the dictionary.Update the dish for Bengaluru.
Remove one city from the dictionary.Use the keys() method to print all city names in the dictionary.Use the values() method to print all dishes in the dictionary.
# 1. Create a dictionary with 5 cities and their famous dishes
karnataka_dishes = {
    "Mysuru": "Mysore Pak",
    "Mangaluru": "Neer Dosa",
    "Hubballi": "Dharwad Peda",
    "Udupi": "Udupi Sambar",
    "Belagavi": "Kunda"
}
print("Initial Dictionary:")
print(karnataka_dishes)

# 2. Add a new city and its dish
karnataka_dishes["Shivamogga"] = "Akki Rotti"
print("\nAfter Adding Shivamogga:")
print(karnataka_dishes)

# 3. Update the dish for Bengaluru
karnataka_dishes["Bengaluru"] = "Bisi Bele Bath"
print("\nAfter Updating Bengaluru:")
print(karnataka_dishes)

# 4. Remove one city from the dictionary
karnataka_dishes.pop("Hubballi")
print("\nAfter Removing Hubballi:")
print(karnataka_dishes)

# 5. Print all city names (keys)
print("\nCities:")
print(karnataka_dishes.keys())

# 6. Print all dishes (values)
print("\nDishes:")
print(karnataka_dishes.values())




